President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring October 3, 2014, as National Manufacturing Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the manufacturing sector in the United States and highlights the contributions of American manufacturers to the nation's economy. The proclamation also calls for programs and activities to be organized to celebrate American manufacturers and encourages Americans to visit a local manufacturer. The proclamation emphasizes the need for research, investment, and a high-tech workforce to ensure America's competitiveness in the 21st-century manufacturing industry. It also mentions the efforts of the federal government and local leaders to support manufacturing and increase access to manufacturing spaces and equipment.